text: William Francis Crosbie (died 11 September 1768) was an Irish Member of Parliament. In 1750 he married Frances Wesley, daughter of Richard Wesley, 1st Baron Mornington, and in 1758 he was elected to succeed his brother-in-law Garret Wesley, 2nd Baron Mornington as Member for Trim in the Irish House of Commons, sitting until 1760.
